{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}
{% import 'macros/macros.html.twig' as macros %}
{% block title %}Help{% endblock %}
{% block body %}
    <div class="col-md-12">
        <div class="card">
            <div class="card-header">Help: Discord Bot</div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <h4>Required bot permissions</h4><hr>
                The bot must have certain permissions to function in Discord. Please make sure the bot has the following permissions in the channel(s) you want it to be active in:
                <ul>
                    <li>Read Messages</li>
                    <li>Write Messages</li>
                    <li>Embed Links</li>
                </ul>

                <br><h4>Using bot commands</h4><hr>
                <strong>!help</strong> will return a message describing how to use all commands.<br>
                Example: <code>!help</code><br><br>

                <strong>!events</strong> will return a list of all upcoming events.<br>
                Example: <code>!events</code><br><br>

                <strong>!event [eventId]</strong> will return information on a specific event.<br>
                Example: <code>!event 123</code><br><br>

                <strong>!attend [eventId] [class] [role]</strong> will set the user to attend a certain event.<br>
                The following options are possible as classes: <i>{{ classes|join(', ') }}</i><br>
                The following options are possible as roles: <i>{{ roles|join(', ') }}</i><br>
                Example: <code>!attend 123 dragonknight tank</code><br><br>

                <strong>!unattend [eventId]</strong> will set the user to not attend a certain event.<br>
                Example: <code>!unattend 123</code><br><br>

                <strong>!timezone [timezone]</strong> will set the user's timezone to the specified value.<br>
                Example: <code>!timezone Europe/Berlin</code><br>
                NOTE: Timezones are <u>case sensitive</u>.<br><br>

                <strong>!characters</strong> will show all the character presets for the user.<br>
                Example: <code>!characters</code><br>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
{% endblock %}